# Student Grievance Redressal System — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A full-featured, production-quality web app built on the existing Next.js project at `c:\Users\santh\my-app\my-app`.

## Pages & Routes

| Route | Description |
|---|---|
| `/grievance` | Student portal home with live stats & feature guide |
| `/grievance/submit` | 4-step grievance intake form |
| `/grievance/track` | Track any grievance by ID |
| `/grievance/feedback/[id]` | Star rating & feedback for resolved cases |
| `/grievance/admin` | Admin dashboard (password: `admin123`) |
| `/grievance/admin/analytics` | Charts & weekly reports |

## Verification

Server logs confirmed all pages return HTTP 200:
- ✅ `GET /grievance 200`
- ✅ `GET /grievance/submit 200`
- ✅ `GET /grievance/track 200`
- ✅ `GET /grievance/admin` (compiled successfully)
- ✅ `GET /grievance/admin/analytics` (compiled successfully)

## Features Implemented

1. **INTAKE** — Multi-step form (4 steps): student info, category selector, description + urgency, review & submit
2. **CLASSIFY** — NLP keyword matching assigns `Critical / High / Medium / Low` priority and auto-extracts tags
3. **ROUTE** — Each category routes to its department/officer; notifications simulated with toast UI
4. **TRACK** — Unique `GRV-2026-XXXX` IDs; full status + SLA timeline view
5. **ESCALATE** — SLA breach detection with banners; admin can manually escalate to HOD/Dean
6. **RESOLVE & FEEDBACK** — Admin resolve modal with notes; 5-star feedback page with emoji indicators
7. **ANALYTICS** — Bar, pie, line, and stacked charts + category summary table with resolution % bars

## How to Use

1. Open `http://localhost:3000/grievance`
2. **Submit**: Click "Submit Grievance" → fill 4 steps → get your `GRV-` ID
3. **Track**: Go to `/grievance/track` → enter your ID (try demo IDs: `GRV-2026-0001` through `GRV-2026-0006`)
4. **Admin**: Go to `/grievance/admin` → password `admin123` → resolve/escalate grievances
5. **Analytics**: Click "Analytics" in admin nav
